DOCTOR STRANGE IN THE MULTIVERSE OF MADNESS fucking rules. I love the MCU, but it can be difficult to get an idea of a director's sensibilities in these movies. This one spins the franchise wheels as expected, but still feels singular to Sam Raimi, and that's so refreshing.

The way he moves the camera, in and out of action sequences, adds an energy to the film that's pretty much unparalleled in the MCU. I also love how it doesn't go overboard with the Multiverse elements, instead choosing to hone in on a few characters and their emotional struggles.

In terms of the movie skirting the line between PG-13 and R, that's nonsense. Blockbusters have been sterilized over the past decade or so. Must've rotted some minds, lol. If kids were okay with Harvey Dent in THE DARK KNIGHT, they should be more than okay with everything here.
